Mar 14 2008 	Great Hotel Challenging Neighborhood	Holiday Inn, Civic Center, San Francisco.We arrived from SFO on BART, and walked one half block from the Civic Center station in the early afternoon.The hotel is clean, with a large comfortable dual-lobby, and is replete with gift shop, cocktail lounge, and limited hour restaurant.Our top floor room was more than adequate, with a nice small balcony and clean bathroom. Safe and comfortable. Room faced the Mission Street side of hotel.Nice supply of coffee/ tea, and a hot water maker.After a quick drink and free appetizers in the lounge, we ventured outside in the early evening, when the neighborhood took on a different complexion.We felt perfectly safe as we walked to Market Street to catch the surface &quot;F&quot; trolley into the Castro. Later that evening, we noticed alot of &quot;street people,&quot; some yelling, some carrying on, but minded our own business. This same F trolley can take you directly to Fisherman's Wharf.Walk one block to 7th Street, and take the #19 bus to Polk Street and California for a stroll through a great &quot;non-touristy&quot; and local neighborhood. Many pubs, shops, bakeries, galleries, jewelry shops, and restaurants. Walk UP Polk from California, NOT the other direction. This same #19 bus will also take you to Ghiardelli Square- right near the Buena Vista, famous for it's Irish Coffee. On it's return trip, it will deposit you directly in front of the Holiday Inn.Basically, come prepared, have a good understanding of the streets, and where you wish to go. Be vigilant, and you shouldn't have any problem- since the hotel is such a short distance from Market Street. If you have very small children, you might wish to choose a different location.The staff is very friendly and accommodating. Our rate included a nice breakfast buffet. We noticed that many rooms on the pool floor had direct access to the outside patio and pool, which may be a good option for a quick morning swim.	
